WEBVTT

00:00.033 --> 00:02.367
-You were planning a wedding?
-Yes, ma'am.

00:03.500 --> 00:04.567
You paid her nothing?

00:05.700 --> 00:08.200
"How dare you call me
before my wedding

00:08.266 --> 00:10.133
asking me for money,"
is what she said.

00:11.367 --> 00:12.667
And hung up in my face.

00:12.734 --> 00:15.166
She was a stressed bridezilla.

00:15.233 --> 00:16.233
Exactly.

00:16.300 --> 00:18.333
[narrator] <i>This is </i>Judy Justice.

00:18.400 --> 00:21.133
[theme music]

00:35.734 --> 00:37.567
[narrator] <i>Makeup artist</i>
<i>Donyale Jones</i>

00:37.633 --> 00:39.700
<i>is suing Erica Fields</i>

00:39.767 --> 00:40.900
<i>for payment of services</i>

00:40.967 --> 00:44.367
<i>and negative reports</i>
<i>to regulatory agencies.</i>

00:44.433 --> 00:46.200
[Kevin] Court, come to order.
All rise.

00:47.333 --> 00:48.800
Have a seat, please.

00:49.266 --> 00:51.433
Good morning, Judge.
We have case number 1025,

00:51.500 --> 00:52.567
Jones versus Fields.

00:52.633 --> 00:53.567
Thank you.

00:53.633 --> 00:54.633
You're welcome.

00:55.734 --> 00:58.266
Ms. Fields, I'm going to
start with you in this case.

00:58.333 --> 00:59.533
You were planning a wedding?

00:59.600 --> 01:01.667
-Yes, ma'am.
-On what date was the wedding?

01:01.734 --> 01:02.700
Sunday, May 30th.

01:02.767 --> 01:03.834
[Judy] Did it take place?

01:03.900 --> 01:04.800
Yes, ma'am.

01:04.867 --> 01:05.834
Is this your husband?

01:05.900 --> 01:07.200
-[Fields] Yes, ma'am.
-Are you happy?

01:07.266 --> 01:09.033
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

01:09.100 --> 01:11.767
Good. Both look very happy.

01:11.834 --> 01:13.734
-[Fields] Two months tomorrow.
-[Judy] Two.

01:13.800 --> 01:15.734
Well, keep counting them
that way with this smile.

01:15.800 --> 01:17.000
Yes, ma'am.

01:17.066 --> 01:18.367
[Judy] And you had
a pretty good wedding day.

01:18.433 --> 01:19.433
-Amazing.
-Yes, ma'am.

01:19.500 --> 01:21.066
Great. When you were
planning the wedding,

01:21.133 --> 01:24.033
according to what I read in
the complaint and your answer,

01:24.100 --> 01:26.600
you were looking for someone to
do the makeup for your wedding.

01:26.667 --> 01:27.600
Yes, ma'am.

01:27.667 --> 01:30.033
[Judy] And you did a search
and you found someone

01:30.100 --> 01:32.233
who came recommended,
and that was the plaintiff.

01:32.300 --> 01:33.233
[Erica] Yes.

01:33.300 --> 01:35.900
And on what date did you
make an appointment to see her?

01:35.967 --> 01:37.300
Well, actually
before that, Your Honor,

01:37.367 --> 01:40.633
I had a phone consultation with her
on Friday, April 23rd.

01:40.700 --> 01:42.433
Okay, and you made
an appointment to see her.

01:42.500 --> 01:45.033
The first appointment
was Sunday, two days later,

01:45.100 --> 01:46.133
the 25th of April.

01:46.200 --> 01:48.300
Okay. And you went
to her place of business.

01:48.367 --> 01:50.066
Was it a studio or her home?

01:50.133 --> 01:51.066
A studio.

01:51.133 --> 01:52.834
[Judy] In the phone conversation
that you had with her

01:52.900 --> 01:55.000
on the 23rd, did you get a quote

01:55.066 --> 01:58.000
for what her services
would be in total?

01:58.066 --> 02:00.333
Yes, ma'am.
So, the verbal quote was up to,

02:00.400 --> 02:02.300
it was for myself on site,

02:02.367 --> 02:04.934
and up to four bridesmaids.
I only needed three.

02:05.000 --> 02:05.867
And how much was that?

02:05.934 --> 02:07.300
Six hundred seventy-five dollars.

02:07.367 --> 02:09.033
And I do have a copy
of that quote.

02:09.100 --> 02:10.033
[Judy] I'm going to get to that

02:10.100 --> 02:11.033
-in a minute.
-Yes, ma'am.

02:11.100 --> 02:12.600
And after you left the studio,
where did you go?

02:12.667 --> 02:14.400
To have engagement photos done.

02:14.467 --> 02:15.533
How long did that take?

02:15.600 --> 02:18.567
The engagement photos?
[laughs] Forever.

02:19.166 --> 02:20.834
Yeah, for about
five or six hours,

02:20.900 --> 02:23.133
we were being photographed
at multiple locations.

02:23.200 --> 02:26.266
Okay, so it would be
fair to say, Ms. Fields,

02:26.333 --> 02:29.100
you had your makeup
done on a Sunday,

02:29.166 --> 02:31.400
which is not
a regular work day.

02:31.467 --> 02:32.967
-Yeah.
-And you had

02:33.033 --> 02:35.467
your makeup done on that Sunday

02:35.533 --> 02:38.033
in order to take
your engagement photos?

02:38.100 --> 02:39.166
-Um...
-That--

02:39.233 --> 02:41.633
-There's no equivocation there.
-Okay.

02:41.700 --> 02:43.633
[Judy] When one takes
engagement photos--

02:43.700 --> 02:45.000
I've been through enough weddings

02:45.066 --> 02:48.400
of my children
and grandchildren to know

02:48.467 --> 02:50.333
that when you take
engagement photos,

02:50.400 --> 02:51.400
you get your makeup done.

02:51.467 --> 02:54.000
I wasn't planning to.
I don't wear makeup typically.

02:54.066 --> 02:55.934
[Judy] Well, whether
you plan to typically,

02:56.000 --> 02:57.266
it is too serendipitous

02:57.333 --> 03:00.600
that out of 365 days a year--

03:00.667 --> 03:02.233
-Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] --that the one day

03:02.300 --> 03:03.667
that you had your test makeup,

03:03.734 --> 03:05.900
you also had
a very long photoshoot

03:05.967 --> 03:08.900
for your engagement party
at multiple locations.

03:08.967 --> 03:10.166
-Yes.
-I can't get that

03:10.233 --> 03:11.166
through my head,

03:11.233 --> 03:13.867
that that was serendipitous
and unplanned by you.

03:13.934 --> 03:15.333
Yes, ma'am.
I did. I apologize.

03:15.400 --> 03:19.066
Right. And now,
I'd like to see from you,

03:19.133 --> 03:21.266
Ms. Jones,
a copy of the contract.

03:23.266 --> 03:26.533
So here is the proposal
and the contract.

03:37.300 --> 03:39.734
[Judy] And can you give me
some idea, Ms. Jones,

03:39.800 --> 03:42.533
of how long the makeup application took?

03:42.600 --> 03:43.767
It usually only takes
like 45 minutes,

03:43.834 --> 03:45.900
but it was during conversation,
so it was a little bit longer.

03:45.967 --> 03:47.700
It was like an hour
and maybe 15 minutes.

03:47.767 --> 03:50.033
Do you remember what time
Ms. Fields got there?

03:50.100 --> 03:51.667
No, I don't remember
exactly what time.

03:51.734 --> 03:52.700
-Her appointment was--
-[Judy] Do you remember

03:52.767 --> 03:54.767
-what time you got there?
-We were supposed to be there,

03:54.834 --> 03:56.900
if I'm not mistaken, at noon.
And I got there--

03:56.967 --> 03:58.867
I text her and told her
I was a few minutes late.

03:58.934 --> 04:00.467
She said it was fine.
I got there.

04:00.533 --> 04:01.900
-[Judy] Okay.
-She was waiting for me.

04:01.967 --> 04:03.934
Were you wearing the clothes
you were going to wear

04:04.000 --> 04:05.367
at the engagement photos?

04:05.433 --> 04:07.300
-No, ma'am.
-Then you had to go home to--

04:07.367 --> 04:09.367
and change in order to get
the engagement photos?

04:09.433 --> 04:10.433
Yes, ma'am.

04:10.500 --> 04:11.367
-What?
-[Jones] No,

04:11.433 --> 04:13.000
she had the clothes on.
She left my studio,

04:13.066 --> 04:14.600
-went straight to the site.
-[Erica] No, ma'am.

04:14.667 --> 04:15.700
-What was she wearing?
-[Erica] I have pictures of

04:15.767 --> 04:17.133
-my engagement photos.
-So, here is the photo

04:17.200 --> 04:18.266
-that she had on.
-[Judy] I'd like to see.

04:18.333 --> 04:19.800
-[Jones] It was-- yeah.
-I'd like to see it.

04:19.867 --> 04:20.900
[Jones] Mm-hmm.

04:26.967 --> 04:28.467
And she also made it
her profile picture.

04:28.533 --> 04:30.834
[Judy] Okay, just a second.
Ms. Fields?

04:30.900 --> 04:31.867
Yes, ma'am.

04:31.934 --> 04:33.133
This is your husband?

04:33.200 --> 04:34.300
-[Erica] Yes.
-[Judy] Do you remember

04:34.367 --> 04:35.333
what color shirt

04:35.400 --> 04:37.433
you were wearing
for the engagement photos?

04:37.500 --> 04:41.000
-Uh, yes, ma'am.
-It was... I'm sorry.

04:41.066 --> 04:42.200
Yes, ma'am.
It was, uh, red.

04:42.266 --> 04:43.467
-[Judy] It was red.
-Yes, ma'am.

04:43.533 --> 04:46.300
And your wife
was wearing polka dot dress

04:46.367 --> 04:48.066
with red, big red rose.

04:48.133 --> 04:49.066
Yes, ma'am.

04:49.133 --> 04:51.033
So, those were
the engagement photo.

04:51.100 --> 04:52.266
-Mm-hmm.
-That's what you were wearing.

04:52.333 --> 04:53.734
Well, you were wearing
that to the studio?

04:53.800 --> 04:55.166
[Erica] No, ma'am.
I left church.

04:55.233 --> 04:57.700
I came to her
in a black one-piece unit,

04:57.767 --> 04:58.734
similar to what she's wearing.

04:58.800 --> 05:00.066
And that's the picture
I sent her

05:00.133 --> 05:01.967
-from the engagement photos.
-[Judy] Okay.

05:02.033 --> 05:02.967
That's not what I was wearing.

05:03.033 --> 05:04.500
This is not what
she was wearing, she said,

05:04.567 --> 05:05.633
-[Erica] No.
-when she came to your studio?

05:05.700 --> 05:06.900
-That is what she was wearing.
-No, I have a picture.

05:06.967 --> 05:08.633
Okay.
Can I see your photo, please?

05:08.700 --> 05:10.367
Yes, ma'am. Unfortunately,
it's in my phone

05:10.433 --> 05:11.834
because I didn't know
it would be privy,

05:11.900 --> 05:13.500
but this is
when I left her studio.

05:13.567 --> 05:14.800
That was in her parking lot.

05:14.867 --> 05:17.066
Okay, great.
I'll just take a quick look.

05:20.633 --> 05:21.633
-[Erica] No rose.
-[Judy] Oh, my goodness,

05:21.700 --> 05:22.633
those are some lashes.

05:22.700 --> 05:23.633
-[Erica] Yeah.
-[inhales sharply]

05:23.700 --> 05:24.633
[audience laughs]

05:24.700 --> 05:27.066
Can I get some of those?

05:27.133 --> 05:28.467
[Erica] Thank you, sir.

05:28.533 --> 05:31.700
[Judy] Okay. I'm reading
this initial retainer,

05:31.767 --> 05:33.967
and Sarah's viewing the contract

05:34.033 --> 05:35.700
'cause I'm gonna look at it
in a second.

05:35.767 --> 05:39.367
It says that when you left,
you were supposed to give her

05:39.433 --> 05:41.200
a retainer of 300 dollars

05:41.266 --> 05:42.300
if you signed the contract.

05:42.367 --> 05:44.100
-Yes.
-Did you give it to her?

05:44.166 --> 05:45.767
Uh, it was verbally agreed,
and I have--

05:45.834 --> 05:46.734
[Judy] No, no, no.

05:46.800 --> 05:47.734
-That's not what I asked.
-I'm sorry.

05:47.800 --> 05:49.834
-No, I did not.
-Did you give her any money?

05:49.900 --> 05:51.100
-Yes.
-[Judy] How much money

05:51.166 --> 05:53.300
-did you give her?
-Thirty dollars cash for a tip.

05:53.367 --> 05:54.767
-[Judy] As a tip?
-Yes.

05:54.834 --> 05:57.467
[Judy] So, other than the tip,
you didn't give her any money?

05:57.533 --> 05:58.467
No, ma'am.

05:58.533 --> 05:59.367
But you did sign the contract.

05:59.433 --> 06:02.133
-Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] Did the contract provide

06:02.200 --> 06:04.667
that at the time
of signing of the contract,

06:04.734 --> 06:07.133
you were supposed
to give her the deposit?

06:07.200 --> 06:08.934
[Erica] No, ma'am.

06:09.000 --> 06:13.333
It just says May 21st
was the entire amount was due.

06:13.400 --> 06:14.967
There's no deposit date.

06:15.033 --> 06:16.066
That's correct.

06:19.767 --> 06:21.233
Okay, well,
it's a little confusing.

06:21.300 --> 06:24.867
It says that the deposit
must be paid in advance.

06:24.934 --> 06:27.800
Well, advance can be a day
in advance or two days in advance.

06:27.867 --> 06:31.000
But there is,
according to the contract,

06:31.066 --> 06:33.734
a 300-dollar deposit
that's due in advance.

06:33.800 --> 06:35.567
-Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] That's non-refundable.

06:35.633 --> 06:36.967
-Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] Did you pay her

06:37.033 --> 06:38.867
-the 300 dollars?
-No, ma'am.

06:38.934 --> 06:40.066
Now tell me why not?

06:40.133 --> 06:41.367
We had a verbal agreement

06:41.433 --> 06:43.533
and later confirmed
by her in writing,

06:43.600 --> 06:45.734
that May 7th was when
the deposit would be due.

06:45.800 --> 06:49.133
Okay. Did you ask her
because you confirmed,

06:49.200 --> 06:50.300
and you signed this contract?

06:50.367 --> 06:51.233
Yes, ma'am.

06:51.300 --> 06:53.266
[Judy] This is my question.
She does your makeup.

06:53.333 --> 06:54.767
-Yes.
-She shows you the contract.

06:54.834 --> 06:56.200
-Yes.
-[Judy] You say that's fine,

06:56.266 --> 06:57.900
because we've already
agreed upon the price.

06:57.967 --> 06:59.433
-Yes, ma'am.
-She needs a deposit

06:59.500 --> 07:00.500
-to hold the date.
-[Erica] Yes.

07:00.567 --> 07:02.834
I want you to understand
how that usually works.

07:02.900 --> 07:04.200
-[Erica] Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] If you're going to

07:04.266 --> 07:05.433
hold the date,

07:05.500 --> 07:07.200
you say I'm going
to sign the contract

07:07.266 --> 07:10.533
and give you a deposit,
the same day, that's what happens.

07:10.600 --> 07:13.133
When you-you took
a wedding venue,

07:13.200 --> 07:15.633
that's what usually happens
when you take a wedding venue.

07:15.700 --> 07:17.567
-[Erica] Yes, ma'am.
-You go, you sign the contract.

07:17.633 --> 07:19.033
On the day you sign
the contract,

07:19.100 --> 07:21.633
you give them a deposit.
I assume that's what you did.

07:21.700 --> 07:24.266
Um, the wedding venue was paid
in full the day we visited.

07:24.333 --> 07:26.066
Okay, but it was paid well before.

07:26.133 --> 07:27.300
-Yes.
-But usually

07:27.367 --> 07:28.867
-you give someone a deposit.
-[Erica] Yes.

07:28.934 --> 07:30.500
And they hold the date,

07:30.567 --> 07:32.233
because this is
a service business.

07:32.300 --> 07:35.100
It's a service venue,
it's a service, makeup artist.

07:35.166 --> 07:40.767
So the 7th of May,
the delay in giving her a deposit

07:40.834 --> 07:45.200
for sure had to be
because you asked for it.

07:45.266 --> 07:46.934
She never gave me a date
for the deposits,

07:47.000 --> 07:49.367
so that's why I asked if I could
just pay it on the 7th.

07:49.433 --> 07:52.500
Well, because you seem
like an intelligent woman.

07:52.567 --> 07:54.600
-[Erica] Yes, ma'am.
-The contract says

07:54.667 --> 07:56.867
that the deposit
must be paid in advance.

07:56.934 --> 07:57.867
-Yes.
-[Judy] By the way,

07:57.934 --> 08:00.433
you should change the contract

08:00.500 --> 08:04.000
by saying the deposit
must be paid

08:04.066 --> 08:06.000
at the time of
signing the contract.

08:06.066 --> 08:07.600
-After this, I have.
-Yes, ma'am.

08:07.667 --> 08:08.867
-[Judy] You did?
-Yes, ma'am.

08:08.934 --> 08:11.567
[Judy] Okay, so you understand
that there was...

08:11.633 --> 08:12.767
[Jones] It's a little shaky, a little.

08:12.834 --> 08:14.200
It's a little shaky.

08:14.266 --> 08:15.934
-Yes.
-Because certainly

08:16.000 --> 08:20.467
she wasn't doing your makeup,
even yours for a tip.

08:20.533 --> 08:23.233
-I agree.
-So, at minimum,

08:23.300 --> 08:26.066
you know
that you owe her the deposit.

08:26.133 --> 08:27.000
-Yes.
-[Judy] At minimum.

08:27.066 --> 08:29.100
-Yes.
-[Judy] So, ultimately,

08:29.166 --> 08:30.533
you breached the contract,

08:30.600 --> 08:33.467
and you breached the contract
by canceling her service.

08:33.533 --> 08:36.467
-She canceled.
-Well, I read your answer.

08:36.533 --> 08:37.767
You tell me in your words

08:37.834 --> 08:39.667
what you want me
to believe happened.

08:39.734 --> 08:42.233
So, when we spoke
over the phone and in studio,

08:42.300 --> 08:43.700
we did verbally agree

08:43.767 --> 08:44.967
that I would pay the deposit May 7th.

08:45.033 --> 08:47.233
She didn't have a definite date
that she wanted it paid. But I--

08:47.300 --> 08:49.433
No, no, no, no.
You understand what I mean.

08:49.500 --> 08:50.734
-[Erica] Okay.
-Ms. Fields,

08:50.800 --> 08:52.767
you're supposed to pay
the deposit

08:52.834 --> 08:55.233
the day you sign the contract.

08:55.300 --> 08:57.033
She didn't issue me
an invoice till May 1st.

08:57.100 --> 08:59.667
See, it's not an invoice.
Uncross your arms.

08:59.734 --> 09:01.100
Don't get angry.

09:01.166 --> 09:04.734
So far, it looks like you're
ahead of the game, right?

09:05.200 --> 09:06.033
Yeah.

09:06.100 --> 09:08.033
You should have
paid the deposit

09:08.100 --> 09:10.266
at the time
you signed the contract.

09:10.333 --> 09:12.900
You knew that it said
300-dollar deposit.

09:12.967 --> 09:15.767
The 375 was paid
on the day of the wedding.

09:15.834 --> 09:16.667
You knew that.

09:16.734 --> 09:19.300
And you knew that, sir,
'cause you came with her, right?

09:19.367 --> 09:20.300
Yes, ma'am.

09:20.367 --> 09:21.533
[Judy] Did you have
any money with you?

09:21.600 --> 09:23.500
-Uh, yes, ma'am.
-[Erica] Yes, ma'am.

09:23.567 --> 09:24.967
[Judy] Well, if you
had money with you,

09:25.033 --> 09:26.834
why didn't you give her a deposit

09:26.900 --> 09:28.133
when you signed the contract?

09:28.200 --> 09:31.467
Then all you had to do
was do $375

09:31.533 --> 09:32.567
on the date of the wedding.

09:32.633 --> 09:34.834
Finished.
You used the makeup.

09:34.900 --> 09:36.633
You went and did
your engagement pictures

09:36.700 --> 09:39.767
using her service,
and didn't pay her anything.

09:39.834 --> 09:43.300
So, at minimum,
you owed her for her service.

09:43.367 --> 09:45.133
-Yes, ma'am.
-[Judy] Which is one hour,

09:45.200 --> 09:49.734
and that charge
was minimally 300 dollars

09:49.800 --> 09:54.100
because she was going to do you
and up to four bridesmaids

09:54.166 --> 09:56.200
for another $375.

09:56.266 --> 09:57.433
I mean, if you think about it,

09:57.500 --> 09:59.934
because that's what
the package included.

10:00.000 --> 10:03.900
Okay. So now, why don't you
tell me the story

10:03.967 --> 10:04.900
that you're going to tell me

10:04.967 --> 10:07.600
about how she breached
the contract?

10:07.667 --> 10:09.734
So, May 3rd, I was at work,

10:09.800 --> 10:12.333
and I received a phone call
from Donyale, out of the blue,

10:12.400 --> 10:14.734
uninitiated by myself,
and she told me

10:14.800 --> 10:16.834
that she had other
business opportunities

10:16.900 --> 10:19.367
for the same day as my wedding
that were willing to pay

10:19.433 --> 10:21.900
before our agreed-upon
deposit due date,

10:21.967 --> 10:23.567
and that she wanted me
to pay her

10:23.633 --> 10:25.000
in advance of our agreement.

10:25.066 --> 10:26.600
And I told her
that I didn't have it.

10:26.667 --> 10:28.400
To be honest,
I got paid that Friday and--

10:28.467 --> 10:29.567
He said he had money.

10:29.633 --> 10:31.300
I didn't ask him for it.
He wasn't my husband yet.

10:31.367 --> 10:33.600
Just a second.
Now you can sit down.

10:35.800 --> 10:36.734
He said he had money.

10:36.800 --> 10:37.734
Yes, ma'am.

10:37.800 --> 10:41.467
[whispers] Over there. Perfect. Perfect.

10:41.533 --> 10:43.667
[theme music]

10:43.734 --> 10:45.433
