21:31.734 --> 21:32.667
Mm-hmm.

21:32.734 --> 21:34.166
[Judy] Now I'm
looking at the next one.

21:39.133 --> 21:44.400
This complaint, complaint
intake monitoring system, CIMS.

21:44.467 --> 21:45.633
That's what
they left at my door

21:45.700 --> 21:47.367
when they finished
their investigation.

21:47.433 --> 21:48.400
[Judy] Just a second.

21:48.467 --> 21:49.867
While they finished
the investigation,

21:49.934 --> 21:52.000
it was received on May 18th.

21:52.066 --> 21:55.867
And May 18th was
two weeks before your wedding.

21:55.934 --> 21:58.767
So, two weeks
before your wedding,

21:58.834 --> 22:00.900
you must have been
more stressed than you were

22:00.967 --> 22:02.567
She continued
to call and text me.

22:02.633 --> 22:05.166
[Judy] Why didn't you
just send her the money?

22:05.233 --> 22:07.100
It became a matter
of principle with you.

22:07.166 --> 22:08.100
It did, honestly.

22:08.166 --> 22:09.700
[Judy] Yeah. Well, you had
nothing else to do.

22:09.767 --> 22:11.800
You couldn't win
against anybody else.

22:11.867 --> 22:14.700
Why did you even in the midst
of planning your first wedding...

22:14.767 --> 22:15.700
How old are you?

22:15.767 --> 22:16.900
-Forty-one.
-[Judy] Forty-one.

22:16.967 --> 22:18.533
In the middle of planning
your first wedding,

22:18.600 --> 22:20.700
you're trying to put
this woman out of business,

22:20.767 --> 22:22.667
whose makeup you loved.

22:22.734 --> 22:24.934
-Well, I got--
-Whose makeup you loved.

22:25.000 --> 22:27.333
It's not that she did
a terrible job.

22:27.400 --> 22:28.700
She got involved at work.

22:28.767 --> 22:30.900
I got in trouble at work
for things that she did.

22:30.967 --> 22:32.633
[Judy] It doesn't matter to me.

22:32.700 --> 22:37.066
The problem, as Shakespeare said,
lies with you.

22:37.133 --> 22:40.200
You looked to get out of paying
for a service.

22:40.266 --> 22:42.333
And I don't think you looked
to get out of paying

22:42.400 --> 22:44.367
for the service
because of the money.

22:44.433 --> 22:46.367
-No, it wasn't the money.
-I think it was because

22:46.433 --> 22:49.133
you were really stressed
with everything else.

22:49.200 --> 22:51.000
-Agreed.
-And you took it out on her.

22:51.066 --> 22:52.767
And I think
that that's unreasonable.

22:52.834 --> 22:55.367
I do. I think that
that's very unreasonable.

22:55.433 --> 22:57.633
And minimally,
since you both agreed

22:57.700 --> 22:59.900
to modify the contract
to 80 dollars,

22:59.967 --> 23:02.166
that's minimally
what the plaintiff would get.

23:02.233 --> 23:04.200
She's suing for
a lot more than that

23:04.266 --> 23:06.200
and she's suing
for reporting her

23:06.266 --> 23:08.033
to the Better Business Bureau,

23:08.100 --> 23:09.834
which is going to give her
a negative rating,

23:09.900 --> 23:14.467
to the place that licenses her,
which is now on file

23:14.533 --> 23:17.233
all because you were
in a snit over the fact

23:17.300 --> 23:19.934
that you were stressed
over planning a wedding.

23:20.000 --> 23:21.200
Do you understand, sir?

23:21.266 --> 23:22.200
Yes, ma'am.

23:22.266 --> 23:24.133
[Judy] It's like if you
lift your spoon out

23:24.200 --> 23:26.600
without rinsing it off
in your house,

23:26.667 --> 23:29.600
and instead of saying,
"Listen, I'm not your maid.

23:29.667 --> 23:32.367
Clean up after yourself,"
which sounds familiar to me,

23:32.433 --> 23:35.266
I've even said it
a couple of times myself,

23:35.333 --> 23:37.667
she packs your bags
and says goodbye.

23:37.734 --> 23:39.066
That would be
an overkill, right?

23:39.133 --> 23:42.400
Yes, ma'am. [laughs]

23:42.467 --> 23:43.867
This was overkill.

23:43.934 --> 23:47.633
Plaintiff is suing in the amount
of 5,000 dollars,

23:47.700 --> 23:49.934
which I think is a bit
of an overkill myself.

23:50.000 --> 23:51.233
Are you still working?

23:51.300 --> 23:53.333
-Currently, yes.
-[Judy] Okay, great.

23:53.400 --> 23:56.300
So, she owes you 80 dollars
for the makeup,

23:56.367 --> 23:57.900
and she owes you
2,000 dollars

23:57.967 --> 24:00.700
for making trouble for you
that she had no right to do.

24:00.767 --> 24:02.934
-Okay.
-[Judy] And that was malicious.

24:03.000 --> 24:04.300
That's the judgment
of the court,

24:04.367 --> 24:05.433
2,080 dollars.

24:05.500 --> 24:07.400
Judgment for the plaintiff,
your counterclaim's dismissed.

24:07.467 --> 24:08.533
We're done. Thank you.

24:08.600 --> 24:09.767
[Kevin] Court adjourned.

24:09.834 --> 24:12.166
[theme music]

24:12.233 --> 24:13.967
I'm elated.
And I'm-I'm thankful

24:14.033 --> 24:15.934
that the judge saw
between all the lies.

24:16.000 --> 24:17.266
She was just unprofessional

24:17.333 --> 24:19.433
and wanted money earlier
than agreed upon.

24:19.500 --> 24:21.367
Guess she was trying to
get me to do something for nothing.

24:21.433 --> 24:24.100
I absolutely do now that
the judge has explained that.

24:24.166 --> 24:25.367
And the way she explained it
made sense.

24:25.433 --> 24:27.867
And I wish I had just given her
the 80 bucks and no tip.

24:27.934 --> 24:29.600
She could have just paid it
and we would have been done.

24:29.667 --> 24:30.734
I'm glad it's over.

24:31.166 --> 24:34.066
So, usually when two people
want to modify a contract,

24:34.133 --> 24:36.467
that usually has to be done
in the same form

24:36.533 --> 24:38.200
as the original contract was,

24:38.266 --> 24:39.967
so in this case,
it was in writing.

24:40.033 --> 24:41.567
So, usually any modification

24:41.633 --> 24:42.834
would also need to be
in writing.

24:42.900 --> 24:44.066
That's true.

24:44.133 --> 24:45.333
So why did you let them
off the hook?

24:45.400 --> 24:48.633
Well, it seemed to me
that the plaintiff

24:48.700 --> 24:50.233
was being very reasonable.

24:50.300 --> 24:53.900
And she said, "All right,
maybe this is not going to work.

24:53.967 --> 24:57.700
Just pay me for the hour
that we spent together."

24:57.767 --> 24:59.967
And that would be
by quantum meruit;

25:00.100 --> 25:01.900
pay for just the work
that was done,

25:01.967 --> 25:03.934
and not for anything
in the future,

25:04.000 --> 25:06.066
which seemed totally reasonable.

25:06.133 --> 25:09.600
And I actually believe
that the defendant said,

25:09.667 --> 25:11.300
okay, and hung up.

25:11.367 --> 25:13.233
The woman sent her a bill
right away.

25:13.300 --> 25:16.600
She didn't pay it and had
no intention of paying it.

25:16.667 --> 25:19.166
The woman agreed to say,
"We're done.

25:19.233 --> 25:20.333
Just pay me the 80 bucks

25:20.400 --> 25:22.667
that I usually charge somebody
for a day's work."

25:22.734 --> 25:24.734
I thought that that was
unconscionable.

25:24.800 --> 25:26.500
I still think
it's unconscionable.

25:26.567 --> 25:30.800
So, that's why
we massaged the rule.

25:32.133 --> 25:33.800
Sometimes you get to do that.

25:33.867 --> 25:34.800
For justice.

25:34.867 --> 25:36.633
For justice.
That's absolutely right.

25:39.033 --> 25:40.233
[narrator]
<i>Have you been cheated?</i>

25:40.300 --> 25:42.700
